                                               TIGERS
Tigers are the largest wildcats in the world. On average size, tigers are 4.8 to 9.5 feet long and weigh 165 to 716 lbs.
Their lifespan is 10-15 years. About 4 species of tigers are extinct in the world and 5 are still not extinct to this day. 
Their range is Turkey and through South SE in Asia. They are endangered by habitat loss (tree logging, etc.) and hunting for skin. 

